This paper deals with fair allocation of goods, which is a classic problem in game theory (cs.GT) and optimization (cs.DS). The paper also proposes algorithms for computing fair allocations, which involves techniques from artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of matroid constraints, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
